---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../components/EmailSignup.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Water Rising"
  description="When the waters rise and South Florida dips below the waterline, three incongruous lives intersect. A speculative fiction novel about faith, certainty, and what we're willing to break to prove we're right."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container novel-container">
      <p class="eyebrow">A Novel</p>
      <h1>Water Rising</h1>

      <div class="premise">
        <p>
          When the waters rise and South Florida dips below the waterline, three incongruous lives intersect.
          A girl who trusts numbers more than people, and the AI who raised her, now learning things it was never designed to know.
          The boy who fishes her out of the water. A man who builds something like salvation.
        </p>
        <p>
          But faith is a long cry from certainty and certainty is its own kind of flood.
          The hardest thing any of them will face isn't the water.
          It's what they're willing to break to prove they're right.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="characters">
        <h2>Characters</h2>
        <!-- TODO: Add character descriptions from Water_Rising/Characters/ in Obsidian vault.
             Characters: Anais Non, Joseph Krutz, Jacob (last name TBD), Dr. Angeline Non.
             Brief — 2-3 sentences each. -->
        <p class="placeholder"><em>Character details coming soon.</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="follow">
        <h2>Follow Along</h2>
        <EmailSignup
          label="Get updates as the novel develops."
          buttonText="Follow along"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .novel-container { max-width: 680px; }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    max-width: none;
  }
  h1 { margin-bottom: var(--space-l); }
  .premise { margin-bottom: var(--space-l); }
  .premise p { font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5em; }
  .characters {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-l);
    padding-top: var(--space-l);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-m); }
  .follow {
    padding-top: var(--space-l);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  .placeholder { color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; }
</style>
